irst President and Simon John (’68 batch), the then Treasurer. Membership was minimal and the association was in its death throes at about the late 80′s when the late Rev. Fr. Pulickal who was the then Director stepped in, took things into his hand and injected new life into the LOBA or Loyola Old Boy’s Association. From then onwards LOBA has grown from strength to strength, gaining in membership mostly under the guidance and drive of Rev. Fr. Joseph Edassery. We are now an integral part of the world wide network of Jesuit Alumni Associations all over the world, and we played a key role in hosting the Fifth National Congress of the Jesuit Alumni Associations of India, on the 7th, 8th, and 9th of September at the Loyola campus. The Past National President of the Jesuit Alumni Associations of India was our very own Alumnus Dr. Santhosh Rollands. Here’s the list of Executive committee members for the year 2012-2013. Contact any of these members to know more about LOBA and its programmes. No. Member Name Designation Contact Number Email ID 1) Manu Cyriac (2005) President 8891769289 manucyriac@gmail.com 2) Hari Shanker R (2006) Secretary 9447325561 hari@harishanker.net 3) Alex Ajith Philip (1987) Vice President 9895046326 alex.philip@gmail.com 4) Somu R (1977) Treasurer 9387711222 somur77@gmail.com 5) Jacob Mathan (1974) Joint Secretary 9847241150 jacmattvm@yahoo.com 6) Rajeev Varghese (Jr.) (2012) Joint Secretary 8089413169  ');";
